{
  "doc_id": "5000",
  "text": "Hyphema is another sign of an unfavorable visual prognosis. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Gupta et al mentioned in a child-based study that the absence of the red reflex could reflect the severity of the injury, and hyphema was the main reason of the absence of a red reflex. [CITATION_3] We found that eyes with hyphema at the time of the initial examination were not prone to achieve a satisfactory VA. Meanwhile, presence of VH had some prognostic value. 1,9 VH might be caused by rupture of the blood vessels in the ciliary body, retina, urea, or sclera, and it could be related to more serious damage of the eye tissues and unfavorable visual outcome.",
